ey.doc: Argument to Failed Primitive in Debugger Session

pc.doc: Function called after a connection has been closed

pm.doc: Handler for OPTIONS, PATCH, PUT and DELETE HTTP Methods

r.doc: If update would be blocked in current context

vs.doc: Hook after a value is set in default namespace

W.doc: Dictionary of IPC handles and bytes waiting in queue

wc.doc: Hook after a websocket connection has been closed

wo.doc: Hook after a websocket connection has been opened

ws.doc: Hook on message arriving at websocket

X.doc: Raw list of all strings with which command line was invoked

x.doc: Command-line arguments as list of strings, cleaned

jd.doc: Serialize object to json, but maps 0w, -0w to null if dictionary [null0w]:1b

k.doc: Deserialize json string to K object

wavg.doc: Weighted average of list, is infix function

bin.doc:
Binary search.
Index of item in sorted where items is greater than item at index, gives -1 if less than first.
infix function

binr.doc:
Binary search right.
Index of first item in sorted where items is lesser than item at index.
infix function

cor.doc: Correlation between list1 and list2, is an infix function

cov.doc: Covariance between list1 and list2, is an infix function

div.doc: Integer division between num1 and num2

enlist.doc: Return a list with one or more argument as items

exp.doc: return e to the power, or null if number is null, is multithreaded primitive

xexp.doc: return base to the power, or null if base is null or negative, is infix and multithreaded primitive

getenv.doc: return environment variable value of symbol

setenv.doc: set environment variable value of symbol to string

hopen.doc: connect to process or file through handle symbol, returns handle

in.doc: returns if items in target_list, is left atomic

insert.doc: insert records into already existing table_symbol, or create table with name symbol with table records

like.doc: returns if symbol/string matches pattern, note regex is not the same

log.doc: natural logarithm of number, is multithreaded primitive

prd.doc: product of list, nulls are treated as 1

sqrt.doc:
returns square root of number, is atomic and multithreaded primitive
returns null if negative or null, 0 if real/float infinity, or square root of largest value

ss.doc: returns the list of starting indices of pattern matches, is infix function

sum.doc: returns the sum of items in list

wsum.doc: returns weighted sum of list, is infix function

tan.doc: returns tangent of numeric in radians

atan.doc: returns arctangent of numeric in radians

within.doc: returns if atom or each item of list is within or equal to bounds

last.doc: return last item of list or dictionary

do.doc: evaluate expression1 expression2 and etc count number of times, returns generic null

if.doc: if test expression evaluates to 1, evaluates expression1, expression2, etc... returns generic null

while.doc: unless test expression evaluates to 0, repeatedly evaluates expression1, expression2, etc... returns generic null

aj.doc: as-of join, boundary time from table1

aj0.doc: as-of join, actual time from table2

ajf.doc: as-of join, fill from LHS if RHS is null, boundary time from table1

ajf0.doc: as-of join, fill from LHS if RHS is null, actual time from table2

all.doc: if list are all non-zero, a non-zero atom, an empty list

any.doc: if list has an non-zero, a non-zero atom

asc.doc:
ascending sort:
sort dictionaries by value
table by first non-key column
mixed list by datatype and by type

iasc.doc: Indexes needed to sort list object in ascending order i.e. first index is the index of the smallest element and asc[l]~l[ iasc[l] ]

xasc.doc: Sort table in ascending order of specified columns, infix function

asof.doc: returns the values of the last row matching the rest of the keys and time <= the time in table 2

attr.doc: return object attributes as symbol vector: sorted, unique, partitioned, true index

mavg.doc: Moving average of int items of list, is infix function

ceiling.doc: Least integer greater than or equal to boolean or numeric in list, is an atomic function

mcount.doc: Moving count of int items in list, is inflix function

cols.doc: List of columns from table, symbol of table variable name or filesymbol

xcol.doc: Rename table with new_cols, in that order, is an infix function

xcols.doc: Reorder table with cols order, is an infix function

scov.doc: Sample covariance between list1 and list2, is an infix function

cross.doc: Cross product between list1 and list2, is an infix function

cut.doc: split list by indices into list of lists

deltas.doc: Difference between consecutive items of list

desc.doc:
descending sort:
sort dictionaries by value
table by first non-key column
mixed list by datatype and by type

idesc.doc: Indexes needed to sort list object in descending order

xdesc.doc: Sort table in descending order of specified columns, infix function

fills.doc: replace nulls with previous non-null values

or.doc: Greater of left and right, is a multithreaded primitive

and.doc: Lesser of left and right, is a multithreaded primitive

mmu.doc: Matrix or dot product of matrix1 and matrix2

mdev.doc: Moving deviation of int items of list, is infix function

differ.doc: Returns boolean list where consecutive values of list differ

each.doc: Applies function to each item of list

peach.doc: Applies function to each item of list but in parallel, if there are subprocesses

ej.doc: Returns table1 joined table2 on cols, where they are equal

ema.doc: Returns exponential moving average with smoothing parameter smoothing, list or atom, is infix function

eval.doc: evaluate parse tree and returns result

reval.doc: evaluate parse tree and returns result, but blocks deletion

fby.doc: returns item list, grouped by indicator then applies aggregator to each group. is infix function

first.doc: return first item of list or dictionary

fkeys.doc: returns a dictionary that maps foreign-key columns to their tables

flip.doc: Transposes object, could be list of lists, dictionary or table

floor.doc: Greatest integer less than or equal to boolean or numeric in list, is an atomic function

get.doc: get the expression of symbol atom or from path

set.doc: set target value to source, target can be global name, file or directory, can also specify compression algorithm

group.doc: Return dictionary where key are elements and values is the list of indices where it is present

gtime.doc: shifts local timestamp to UTC time

ltime.doc: shifts UTC timestamp to local time

hcount.doc: return size of file symbol in bytes

hdel.doc: delete the file or folder and echo input

hclose.doc: close connection handle, this is should be an integer from hopen

hsym.doc: prefix symbols with colon if it does not beign with one

ij.doc: returns table1 joined on common values of key columns of table2, and the columns should share the same name

ijf.doc: returns table1 joined on common values of key columns of table2, and the columns should share the same name

inter.doc: return common values of list1, list2, for dictionaries, uses common values

inv.doc: inverts non-singular matrix using LU decomposition

key.doc:
Returns dictionary keys
keys of a keyed table
files in a folder
if a file exists
if name is defined
type of vector
enumerator of list
if an integer, same thing as til

keys.doc: return primary key columns of table

xkey.doc: set columns as primary keys in table

lj.doc: returns left join of table1 on table2, table2 should have keyed columns that match names in table1

ljf.doc: returns left join of table1 on table2, table2 should have keyed columns that match names in table1

load.doc: load object from binary file_symbol, in directory recursively searches for objects

rload.doc: load splayed table from binary directory_symbol

xlog.doc: return the base logarithm of number, is infix function

lower.doc: return string or symbol to lowercase

upper.doc: return string or symbol to uppercase

lsq.doc: returns the least squares solution that minimizes x - (x lsq y) mmu y; rows of design matrix should be independent; lsq uses Choleski decomposition

mmax.doc: return moving maximum of last int consecutive items in list

md5.doc: return as a byestream its MD5 (message-digest algorithm 5) hash

meta.doc: return meta data of table or table_symbol, meta data included column name c, data type t, foreign key f, attribute a

mmin.doc: return moving minimum of last int consecutive items in list

mod.doc: return nums mod bases, and is a multithreaded primitive, atomic function

neg.doc: return negation of number, if null returns null

next.doc: shifts list forward, last element is null since there is no next element

prev.doc: shifts list backward, first element is null since there is no previous element

xprev.doc: shifts list by shift amount, negative number shift forward first or last shift elements are null

not.doc: return 0b if object is not equal to zero, 1b otherwise, is an atomic function and a multithreaded primitive

null.doc: return 1b if object is null, is an atomic function and a multithreaded primitive

over.doc: if function is univariate, keeps applying function until value stops changing, and output final result; if function is bivariate, and object is a list, applies function on consecutive values accumulating and return final result

scan.doc: if function is univariate, keeps applying function until value stops changing, and output all intermediate result; if function is bivariate, and object is a list, applies function on consecutive values accumulating and return intermediate results

parse.doc: if expression is a q-function returns the lambda, else returns the parse tree

pj.doc: left join table1 and table2 on keyed common table2 columns, and sums values of common columns

prds.doc: return cumulative products of its items

prior.doc: return list of results of function applied to each item and the item preceding it, function should be bivariate or more

rand.doc: return random item in list or a random atom of same type

rank.doc: return the index of each item in ascending sort, i.e. first entry is the position of the first item in the list when sorted asc.

ratios.doc: returns ratios between consecutive items of list

raze.doc: joins or concatenates all items of list and returns final result

read0.doc:
reads file as list of strings delimited by LF or CRLF and delimiters are removed
 with file descriptor (file;start;length), can control which chunks are read

read1.doc: reads file as bytes, with file descriptor (file;start;length), can control which chunks are read

reciprocal.doc: returns the reciprocal of number, atomic and multithreaded primitive

reverse.doc: returns lists in reverse order, dictionaries with reverse key order and tables with reverse column order

rotate.doc:
returns lists rotated by shift items, left for positive and right for negative
dictionaries with rotates key order
tables rotates column order

save.doc: saves global variable v to path and depending on ext creates a different object, returns filename

show.doc: formats object and displays it at the console stdout, returns identity function

signum.doc: returns sign of number, return -1 for nulls, is atomic and multithreaded primitive

ssr.doc: returns string where each matching pattern substring is replaced by string or function[matched_substring]

string.doc: returns object as a string, works on all datatypes, is atomic

sublist.doc: returns sublist of list by index int or pair (start; length), is guaranteed to be a subset

sums.doc: return cumulative sums of list items

msum.doc: Moving sum of int items of list, is infix function

sv.doc:
Encode list with scalar:
For list of strings, joins string with delimiter scalar
For sym lists, joins into new symbol seperated by period when scalar is empty symbol, but for filepath components it seperates by /
On int lists, evaluates at base scalar
For byte or bits list, converts to integer

tables.doc: returns list of tables as symbols in namespace

til.doc: returns list of the first n natural numbers, from 0 to n-1

trim.doc: return list without leading and trailing nulls

type.doc: return type of object as a short int

uj.doc:
if table1 and table2 have matching key columns, return table1 with table2 values filling with nulls
else insert table2 into table1 filling with nulls

ujf.doc:
if table1 and table2 have matching key columns, return table1 with table2 values filling with nulls
else insert table2 into table1 filling with nulls

union.doc: return distinct union of items in list1 and list2, could also be atoms

ungroup.doc: if table has cells as list but for any row, the lists are the same length, returns normalized table with one row for each item of a lists

upsert.doc: append or overwrite records to table or symbol of table name, returns new table

value.doc:
returns value of object:
dictionary: list of values
symbol atom: value of symbol in default namespace
enumeration: corresponding symbol vector
string: evaluates string as code
list: calls first element with remaining as arguments
projection: function followed by arguments
compositions: list of composed values
derived function: value of iterator
operator: internal code
view: list of metadata
lambda: the structure
file symbol: content of datafile

views.doc: returns sorted list of views currently defined in default namespace

vs.doc: partition a symbol, string or bytestream, or encode a vector from an atom or a matrix from a vector

where.doc:
if list is boolean, returns indices where 1
if list of non-neg integers, returns list where index appears number of times equal to value something similar for keys in dictionary

xbar.doc: returns number rounded to the nearest multiple of base

xgroup.doc: returns table grouped by columns as primary keys

xrank.doc: returns for each item in list the bucket it falls into, from 0 to bucket_count-1

addr.doc: return hostname symbol as an integer

b6.doc: upper- and lower-case alphabet and numerics

bv.doc:
construct dictionary .Q.vp of table schemas for tables wtih missing partitions.
With argument, use prototype from first partition instead of last

bvi.doc: same as .Q.bv but scans only new partitions

chk.doc:
fill HDB
fills tables missing from partitions using the most recent partition as template

cn.doc:
return count partitioned table
Populates .Q.pn cache

D.doc: In segmented DBs, return a list of the partitions, conformant to .Q.P

dd.doc: returns joined symbol and symbol or string, shorthand for ` sv x, `$string y

def.doc: merges default parameter dictionary with second argument which is the output of .Q.opt .z.x

f.doc: return number formatted as float to precision decimal places

fc.doc: returns result of function on each item in list, uses parallel execution

ff.doc: returns table with new columns with all nulls, if column name already in table, does not do anything

fk.doc: return ` if column is not a foreign key or table as symbol

fmt.doc: return number as string of length characters with exactly decimal places

fpn.doc: reads chunks of complete \n delimited records from pipe and applies function to each record.

fps.doc: reads chunks of size 131000 bytes complete \n delimited records from pipe and applies function to each record.

fsn.doc: reads chunks of complete \n delimited records from file and applies function to each record.

fs.doc: reads chunks of size 131000 bytes complete \n delimited records from file and applies function to each record.

ft.doc:
apply simple
applies function for simple table to keyed table and returns table with as many key columns as keyed_table

fu.doc:
apply unique
applies unary_function to distinct elements of list then populates the list assuming it is a true function.

gc.doc: garbage collects and returns the amount of bits freed

gz.doc:
GZip
if meta is ::, returns if zlib is loaded
if meta is a string, returns unzipped string
if meta is ( compression level; string ) returns zipped string with compression level

hg.doc: returns result of HTTP[S] GET query at URL

host.doc: returns int IP address as symbol

id.doc: Sanitize symbols of improper q names

ind.doc: return partitioned table with only max number of rows

j10.doc: return string encoded as binhex, the alphabet .Q.b6

j12.doc: return string encoded as base 36, the alphabet .Q.nA

x10.doc: return decoded binhex string, the alphabet .Q.b6

x12.doc: return decoded base 36 string, the alphabet .Q.nA

l.doc: loads directory recursively as in load but in default namespace

ld.doc: Exposes logic used by load, returns file strings grouped into blocks

li.doc:
load partitions
in the current hdp, any partitions which are in partitions and on disk

lo.doc: Load a database without changing directory and or loading scripts in database

MAP.doc: Keeps partition mapped to avoid overhead of repeated file system calls

opt.doc: returns command-line as a dictionary, using the output of .z.x, defaults can be added using .Q.def

P.doc: In segmented DBs, returns a list of the segments

par.doc: returns expected directory path of table of that date

PD.doc: In partioned DBs, returns partition locations

pd.doc: In partioned DBs, returns partition locations as modified by .Q.view

pf.doc: In partitioned DBs, returns the partition field, possible values are `date`month`year`int

pn.doc: In partitioned DBs, returns a dictionary of cached partition counts

prf0.doc: code profilereturns a table representing a snapshot of the call stack at the tiem of the call in another kdb+ process

pt.doc: returns a list of partitioned tables

qp.doc: returns if object is partitioned table, if splayed returns 0b, else 0

qt.doc: returns if object is a table, else 0b

s.doc: returns object as formatted plain text, as used by console

sbt.doc: returns backtrace as a string formatted for display

sha1.doc: returns string as a bytestream its SHA-1 hash

t.doc:
type letters
list of chars indexed by datatype numbers

trp.doc:
extend trap at
returns unary function with arg1, if error returns binary function called with error string and backtrace object

trpd.doc:
extend trap
returns function with args, if error returns binary function called with error string and backtrace object

ts.doc:
time and space
equivalent to \ts .[arg1;arg2], returning the time in miliseconds and space in bytes used for applying arg1 on arg2

ty.doc:
type
returns type of list as a character code, lower case for lists, and upper case for uniform lists, else blank

u.doc:
date based
in segmented DBs, return 1b if each partition is uniquely found in one segment
in partitioned DBs, return 1

V.doc:
table to dict
returns a dictionary of its column name to column values

v.doc:
value
if filepath, returns splayed table stored at symbol
if any other symbol, returns global named symbol
anything else, returns input

view.doc:
subview
filters any future queries to partitioned dbs with the input filter values

vp.doc:
missing partitions
in partitioned DBs, returns a dictionary of table schemas for tables with missing partitions

w.doc:
memory stats
returns the memory stats from \w into a more readable dictionary

x.doc:
non-command parameters
set by .Q.opt, a list a non-command parameters from the command line, where command parameters are prefixed by -
